{
  "stem": "26142.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The languages that were used in-- in Torun, and not only in Torun, the whole Carpathian, in-- in the Jewish homes was Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The second language was, of course, Ruthenian because the majority of the people, like I said, 90% of the people were Ruthenian.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They call themselves, at that time, small Russians.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know how-- how-- now it is incorporated into the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- but it-- the-- the language, the small Russian, the way it was spoken in the Carpathian, is a slight bit bit different than the real Ukraine, because I was in the Ukraine later.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But all Slavic languages, if you know one, you can understand the rest of them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, there are also, of course, the official language was Czech in-- in-- in the offices.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You were able to, in the Carpathia, you were able to use those two languages, your Ruthenian and-- and Czech.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we-- we-- my-- my oldest brothers, both Moshe and Eliezer, since they-- and my father-- since they were under Austria-Hungary, they knew Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I didn't hear the language, and they didn't speak it at home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They spoke it until 1900 and-- for, no, more than 14.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, the war ended in '18. 1914 it broke out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think in one year, in 1917, I think, I remember they were talking in the house that my oldest brother was drafted in the Austria-Hungarian, and my father was drafted in it.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So they were-- they-- they knew a little bit Hungarian, but I didn't know Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "All we know was mother tongue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My mother tongue is Yiddish, and-- and what we learned in Czech school, the-- the Czech and Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And of course, since I went to Hebrew school in Cheder that-- that you learn the Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
